1
00:00:03,320 --> 00:00:07,280
I heard there's a cabin up north...
Moshe! Amazing, inside a cave.

2
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:11,080
I'm not Jesus in a cave,
not in a wooden cabin or a tent in the desert.

3
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:12,800
I haven't done anything wrong to anyone.

4
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:15,600
Why bad? I'm just trying to find something that will make you happy.

5
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:18,480
So maybe we should fly abroad?
-What fly?

6
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:21,440
What, to Paris?
Let's fly to Los Angeles for Efrat,

7
00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:23,320
The girls are already grown up.
-What Los Angeles?

8
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,600
I just got a little bonus.
I didn't win the lottery.

9
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,960
So, what do you want to do with the money?
-I don't know yet.

10
00:00:28,080 --> 00:00:31,320
Whatever I feel like. First of all, meat.
I want to eat a good steak.

11
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:33,960
You got 3,200 shekels and all you want is a steak?

12
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:37,800
Do you know how long it's been since I
had a good steak? Like, properly aged.

13
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:42,840
A thick ribeye like that,
maybe with some coarse salt on it...

14
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:45,560
A steak you know you didn't just pay 90 shekels for.

15
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,600
I want to chow down on a cow at "A.V."

16
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:49,480
After that, do whatever you want
with the leftover bonus.

17
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:52,960
Alright, fine, so you have it in short.
Call "A.V." and book a table for yourself.

18
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,880
For you?
-Come on, what do you want?

19
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,720
They only have pieces of cow to eat there.

20
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:59,520
There's nothing for the girls to eat.
-So what, am I supposed to eat alone?

21
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:02,600
Take Manny. You always said
he's your favorite in the family,

22
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:05,080
and now he just had a son and he loves meat like you do,

23
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:07,560
so that's cool. Go, go with Manny
and chow down on a cow.

24
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:09,840
What is it, how much will it cost you?
-Honestly, it's doable.

25
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:14,040
But that doesn't get you off the cabin, right?
Alright, let's go. Find parking.

26
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:21,720
Look at me, look at me...

27
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:36,240
This belongs to that, it's going to green.

28
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,160
Dad, pass me the next cable.

29
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,600
Here, this is for the camera.
-For the camera.

30
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,800
I don't get why you guys don't buy a laptop.

31
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,800
When was the last time you surfed the internet?

32
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:50,960
We need to move forward.
-Sir, I'm doing a Kiddush here

33
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:54,320
from my living room in Israel
with my daughter Efrat in Los Angeles

34
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:57,680
via Skype. Is that advanced enough for you?

35
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:01,120
Here it is...
-Right?

36
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,040
This one for the remote.

37
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:06,320
For the mouse.
-Mouse.

38
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:08,759
That's it. It's connected, I think.
Just need to turn it on.

39
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,520
Can you just come sit?
I wanted to ask you something.

40
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:12,680
Sure.

41
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:17,240
I wanted to ask you something sensitive
about the internet.

42
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,480
Do you know who Itzik the Happy is?

43
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,800
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

44
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,160
Shabbat Shalom.

45
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,600
Hey, what's up?

46
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,600
What's new?
-Shabbat Shalom, Dad.

47
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,080
What's up? What's the week like?
-Are you doing Kiddush with Efrat?

48
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:33,200
Yeah, just need to turn it on and that's it.
-Is everything connected?

49
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,200
Yeah.
-Then come, come here for a sec,

50
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,320
I want to talk to him about something.

51
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,360
Tell me, are they here with the little one?
-Yeah, they're in the kitchen.

52
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:39,640
Great. What's up, Dad? What's the week like?
-You know how it is.

53
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:42,400
They say anyone over 60
who doesn't feel any pain,

54
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,480
it's a sign they're dead.

55
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,920
Alright, I'm going to say hi to Mom and Alin.

56
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,040
Dad, do you need help?

57
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:50,320
No, no. I don't need help.

58
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:53,920
Why do you think I'm limited in any way?

59
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:58,240
You don't need to be a professor to press a button

60
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,880
that says "Ooh" and "Oof." Oh, here it is.

61
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,120
What's up, Shushu?

62
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,480
Listen, you love meat, so I thought I'd invite you.

63
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:09,320
Let's go out tomorrow night, just you and me,
to grab a bite. We'll go for a steak.

64
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,200
Really good quality at A.V. I'm ordering.

65
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:13,360
I never say no to meat, it's a principle.
-Of course.

66
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,720
It's a deal?
-Deal.

67
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:17,760
Good thing I have ears, or else
the smile would tear my face apart.

68
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:20,480
Alright, I'm just going to confirm this with Alin...
-What do you need to confirm?

69
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,480
95% sure it's a done deal.
-Oh, then I'm calling A.V.

70
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,040
95% sure of a reservation?
-Cool.

71
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,000
Awesome.
-Awesome.

72
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,400
Just keep it quiet with Elio, okay?

73
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:30,080
I want it to be just you and me.
You know this family. It's...

74
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,440
Of course.

75
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:35,120
Hi, I want to reserve a steak for tomorrow.
A place. Sorry.

76
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:48,160
How sweet, look at him laugh.

77
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:52,040
Everyone says he has the same laugh as Manny.

78
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:56,040
Tell me, he's in the top percent, right?

79
00:03:57,040 --> 00:04:00,000
Sure. Manny wasn't small either, right? It's in your genes.

80
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:03,640
Yeah, but he's a bit bigger
than Manny was at that age.

81
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:07,200
Knock on wood. Wow, wow, wow,

82
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,600
My sweetie, my sweet.
-Alright, healthy kid.

83
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,280
My little cutie, my small child,

84
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:18,360
Tiny tot, cutie pie, my little darling.

85
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,279
Don't listen to nonsense.

86
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:25,360
So, what happened to Dad?
-Oh, I don't know,

87
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:28,640
I have no idea. Ever since Elio and Manny came, he's been like this,

88
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:29,960
giving me the cold shoulder, not talking to me.

89
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:32,840
What’s he upset about now?
-I don’t know, no clue,

90
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:35,640
only God knows.
-Elio, can I have a moment?

91
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:42,320
Two on the bar, and if there’s a change,
I’ll let you know. Thanks.

92
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,520
There’s a problem with the computer software.

93
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:52,200
What’s the problem?
-What’s the problem...

94
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:54,560
Oh, also, acting all cool, being dismissive.

95
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,880
If I say there’s a problem, then there’s a problem.

96
00:04:56,960 --> 00:05:00,600
And what about her?
-That I turned on the computer and nothing happens.

97
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,000
Are you sure you turned it on?

98
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:08,120
Did you press the power button?
-Stop messing with my head.

99
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:11,600
I pressed the right button.
-The big red one with the line on it.

100
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:16,600
Listen, I pressed the big button
that turns on the whole computer. Got it?

101
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:19,880
The one with the yellow sticker I put on

102
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:23,240
and I wrote "On" and "Off" on it. Got it?

103
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,800
It’s closed.
-What’s closed? What’s closed? It’s open.

104
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,800
Look, what’s wrong with you?
-What’s with the face?

105
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:29,720
I feel bad for her.

106
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,440
She’s home alone with the baby all day.
-Manny...

107
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,080
Do me a favor, both of you, okay?

108
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,720
Stop messing around, look at what's happening here?

109
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:38,480
Please. I don’t want
Efrat waiting there in Los Angeles

110
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:42,320
with her whole family because that’s not respectful.

111
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:45,640
Alright, alright, Dad. Shai, check
that everything's connected properly.

112
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,920
No problem. Worst case, if we can’t connect,

113
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:50,680
we can look at Orna a couple of times.
-What happened to you? Efrat is way prettier.

114
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,880
Efrat is way prettier? Oh, twins.

115
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:56,880
She’s way more into me.
-Well, the last time I saw

116
00:05:56,960 --> 00:06:00,000
Efrat was when she gave birth to the... to Manny?

117
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,440
Yael.
-Gizelle.

118
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,200
Even then, she was a knockout.

119
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:04,920
So, does it make a noise when it’s on?

120
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,560
-Dad, tell me,
did you even turn on the screen?

121
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,680
What message?
-This screen.

122
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:13,360
What, isn’t it automatic?
-No, Dad, it’s not automatic.

123
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:14,680
Here, the power button is right here.

124
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,040
I need a sticker.

125
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,400
Well, anyway, there’s a problem because it won’t turn on.

126
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,920
Yeah, there’s probably an issue with the computer software.

127
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,640
So that’s what I said, there’s a problem.
When I say there’s a problem, there’s a problem.

128
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,200
Oh, thank God.

129
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:31,320
Your dad is a penny pincher. Oh, thank God,
do you know what time it is?

130
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:34,280
Go get dressed. I thought you’d help me a bit.
-Okay, just a sec,

131
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,880
How’s it going, babe?
-What’s up, sis?

132
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:39,080
All good, did you see the baby? What a giant!
-Why a giant?

133
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:43,080
He’s not a giant,
but you have to admit he’s big.

134
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:46,120
Big?
-He’s not big. He just has big bones.

135
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,320
Wait, what’s better? A kid that’s too small?

136
00:06:48,960 --> 00:06:51,240
He’s a healthy kid.
-That’s not a kid, that’s a fridge.

137
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,440
Meirav...

138
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,320
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

139
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:57,440
Oh, here come Moshe and Orna.
Go get dressed, you’re half-naked.

140
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,160
Go, go, before Ilana tears you apart.

141
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,600
What’s up, Moshe?
-So, have you uploaded Efrat yet?

142
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,160
No, not yet, there’s a problem with the computer software.

143
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,720
You need to turn it off and on,
it always works. Move aside. Let me.

144
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,520
Enough, Moshe, Moshe, can you chill? We just did a restart.

145
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,560
And it didn’t start.
-No.

146
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:12,720
I always kick it
a little! A little kick, it always works.

147
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,640
That’s the advice they gave at tech support?

148
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,360
What’s the deal?
-You know, but what...

149
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,200
What’s going on with you guys? How’s the little one?

150
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:22,680
Honestly, thank God. We finished
renovating his room, it turned out amazing.

151
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:26,800
That’s great. So maybe we’ll come over tomorrow?
Moshe, me and the kids?

152
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:30,120
No, not tomorrow. Manny is going out with Shai.

153
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,560
Really?
-To which restaurant, I know. Something with cows.

154
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,680
Cows.
-Yeah.

155
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,680
Nice.

156
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:38,360
I don’t get why it’s not working.
-Give me a sec, Shai, I’ll handle it.

157
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:41,240
I had the same thing at home.
It’s nonsense, it’s a "BBS" issue.

158
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:43,240
What’s "BBS"?
-There’s no such thing.

159
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:44,960
Why do you say there isn’t? Here, look.

160
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,880
Hey, oh
-What?

161
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,640
What are you doing? He’s trying to start the computer.

162
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:52,880
What are you... stop kicking, stop kicking.
-It always works, Silvan.

163
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:56,560
What’s wrong with you? I’m going to get a manual.

164
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,080
Hold on! Keep this horse until I get back.

165
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,000
Helen...
-What?

166
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,040
Moshe...

167
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,320
Shabbat Shalom, babe.
-Shabbat Shalom.

168
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,800
Tell me, what am I hearing?

169
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,000
I don’t know, Mediterranean music usually. Right?

170
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:10,960
Tell me, what’s this story about Manny and Shai dating?

171
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:15,320
What... what’s the story... just, with Ilan...

172
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:18,760
They’re going to some steak place,

173
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,840
“Yeah, Moshe! One of those Saturday night spots.

174
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:23,440
You know, it’s half restaurant, half bar, something...

175
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:26,720
Just a place to raise a glass,
a place like that, a fancy place.

176
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,520
Oh, and Moshe doesn’t go because it’s fancy?

177
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:32,120
What?
-So why doesn’t Moshe go?

178
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:35,679
You know, you don’t see it on him
but inside he’s sensitive, sensitive,

179
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,640
He’s like porcelain in an elephant shop.

180
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:41,080
Tell me, what’s wrong with you? What,
it’s not like it was planned for weeks,

181
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,640
It's right here on the way, closed.
-So what?

182
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,960
You know, Shai, he felt like having meat
so he also invited Mabi.

183
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,480
Do you want him to invite Moshe too?
No problem,

184
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,920
he'll invite Moshe too.
-Great, because I won't have the energy

185
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,440
for his whining at home:
"Nobody loves me,

186
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:54,680
why did they say this and that?"
-No problem, no problem, sis.

187
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:57,400
It's on me, just relax.
-I'm going to grab a snack.

188
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:03,520
Shai, come here for a sec, babe. Come on, just a moment.

189
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:08,840
Hey, where's Mom?
-How should I know?

190
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:10,880
Give me that, give me that.
-No, I don't want to.

191
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:13,320
Sali? Sali, are you here?

192
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:19,400
You're not talking to me? Are you playing
childish games with me?

193
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:24,200
Just so you know, I can play
just as well as you can.

194
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,720
No wonder you don't know them.

195
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,360
Silvan.
-That's Tripov's.

196
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:45,360
He found it in the closet.
-What's that?

197
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:48,440
It's the old "iPod."
-How Grandpa Menachem loved them...

198
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:53,720
I had tons of tapes here, I really did.

199
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:57,600
Of Aris Su, of Trifonas, of Elikhi, there was...

200
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:07,640
Everything okay?
-Yeah, everything's fine.

201
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,200
And you?

202
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,000
Everything's fine.

203
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:16,760
So all this time you were... here?

204
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:20,600
Why, did something happen there?
-No, nothing. Nothing.

205
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:24,680
What are you looking for?
-What do you think I'm looking for?

206
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:28,280
I don't think. That's why
I'm asking. What are you looking for?

207
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:31,080
I'm looking for the computer manual.

208
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,240
It's over there.
-No, it's not there.

209
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,320
The helper stole it.

210
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:41,520
Look near the box of records.
I'm going back to the kitchen.

211
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:44,120
So what? So... I'm not...

212
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:47,880
Is it cheerful enough?
-Not really.

213
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:51,400
Moshe is coming with you tomorrow too.
-What? Why?

214
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,480
Because, Alin told Orna,
and Moshe will start crying

215
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:55,560
and I'll get the blame and I don't want that.
-But what...

216
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:57,120
And you can't put all that on Orna
for the whole amount,

217
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,240
so you're inviting Moshe too.
-No, I just wanted...

218
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:01,240
Come on, what's your deal? Why are you making a big deal out of this?

219
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:03,880
It's just Moshe. He's a little guy,
how much can he eat?

220
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:07,520
What? Did he take your plate?
He barely eats a quarter of a chicken himself.

221
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,600
I'll go change the order.
-Thanks, babe.

222
